article.headline: Howard 65, Maryland-Eastern Shore 63
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Will Gant scored 14 points on 5-of-9 shooting, including 4-of-7 from 3-point range, and Howard rallied for a 65-63 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday. Reserve Kandi Mukole scored eight of his 12 points in the second half for the Bison (5-5, 2-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who trailed by seven midway through the second half. Darryl Hudson added 10 points, all after intermission, and nine rebounds. Ed Tyson scored 16 points for the Hawks (1-5, 0-1). Antonio McMillion and Jesse Brooks had 14 each. The Hawks shot 46.4 percent in the first half to Howard's 39.3 percent, but led by just two at halftime, 33-31. Maryland-Eastern Shore was perfect on free throws at halftime, but the Hawks missed five of their final six free-throw attempts.
